# RuneForged Data and Save Rules

## Data discipline
- Keep item schema, rune schema, enemy schema, and save schema stable unless explicitly changing the contract.
- Prefer additive schema changes over destructive ones.
- Reuse existing field names where possible.

## Save compatibility
- Before changing persisted structures, check docs/save-format.md if it exists.
- Preserve backward compatibility whenever practical.
- If a migration is required, implement the smallest safe migration path.
- Clearly call out new save keys, changed keys, removed keys, and default fallback behavior.

## Inventory and equipment assumptions
- Stackable materials and consumables may share logic.
- Unique gear, relics, and special rolled items should not be silently forced into stack behavior unless explicitly specified.